Start
/ Main test runner for Channel tests
/ Tests the PLang channel system: output routing, handlers, content type configuration

- write out 'Channel Tests - Starting...'
- write out ''

/ Test 1: Channel Handler Registration
- call !TestChannelHandler
- write out 'Test 1: Channel Handler Registration - PASSED'

/ Test 2: Configure Output Content Type
- call !TestConfigureOutput
- write out 'Test 2: Configure Output Content Type - PASSED'

/ Test 3: Output Levels (info, warning, error)
- call !TestOutputLevels
- write out 'Test 3: Output Levels - PASSED'

/ Test 4: Error Channel Handler
- call !TestErrorChannel
- write out 'Test 4: Error Channel Handler - PASSED'

- write out ''
- write out 'All 4 Channel tests passed!'
- write out ''
- write out 'Note: Ask channel override tests are in AskChannel.goal'
- write out 'They can be run separately with: plang run AskChannel'

TestChannelHandler
/ Register a handler for a custom channel and verify it captures output
/ Use caching to share state between handler and test
- cache '' for 10 minutes, to 'testCapturedCache'
- on channel 'user', 'testlog', call !HandleTestOutput
- write out 'captured message' to user channel testlog
/ Get the cached value that was set by the handler
- get cache 'testCapturedCache', write to %testCaptured%
- if %testCaptured% is not 'captured message', throw error 'TestChannelHandler failed: expected captured message, got %testCaptured%'

HandleTestOutput
/ This handler intercepts output sent to user channel testlog
/ Use cache to store the captured content so parent can access it
- cache %content% for 10 minutes, to 'testCapturedCache'

TestConfigureOutput
/ Configure output content type and verify it was set
- configure output to 'application/json'
/ If we get here without error, the configuration worked
- write out '  - Configure output to JSON: OK'

TestOutputLevels
/ Test writing with different output levels
- write out 'info level message', level info
- write out 'warning level message', level warning
/ If we get here without error, levels work
- write out '  - Output levels work: OK'

TestErrorChannel
/ Register handler to intercept error-level output
/ Use caching to share state between handler and test
- cache '' for 10 minutes, to 'errorCapturedCache'
- on channel 'user', 'error', call !HandleErrorOutput
- write out 'test error message', level error, status code 500 to user channel error
/ Get the cached value that was set by the handler
- get cache 'errorCapturedCache', write to %errorCaptured%
- if %errorCaptured% does not contain 'test error message', throw error 'TestErrorChannel failed: error not captured, got %errorCaptured%'

HandleErrorOutput
/ This handler intercepts error messages
/ Use cache to store the captured content so parent can access it
- cache %content% for 10 minutes, to 'errorCapturedCache'
